title: Falling from the Sky: Flight 174 (1995)[True story] DVDrip
description:

Flight 174
Free Fall
Freefall
 <a href="

True story of a new Canadian Boeing 767 airliner that ran out of fuel in mid-air. This incident has later been used for pilots in flight simulators, and almost none of them have succeeded in landing the plane safely.

The captain handled the situation with his previous experience flying sailplanes, and by remembering an old airfield that was no longer found on the maps.

This has been among my favourite films since I first recorded it from television in May 1997, and I was thrilled to learn that it was now available on DVD. However, picture quality on the DVD is not first-class with minor disturbances, but I made my best out of it.

Original fullscreen, 624x464, AC3, good stereo sound.
Burn tested, runs well in my DivX player.
